House of Representatives member-elect for Irepo-Oore­lope- Olorunspgo Federal Con­stituency, Prince Olaide Lateef Muhammed, has felicitated Femi Gbajabiamila over his appointment as the Chief of Staff to President Bola Ahmed Tinubu. The chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC) from Oyo State, in his goodwill message said Gbajabiamila’s appointment did not come as a surprise to Nigerians, particu­larly the political elite going by his political antecedents. Mohammed also commend­ed President Tinubu for appoint­ing one of Nigeria’s finest politi­cians as his Chief of Staff. The APC stalwart also de­scribed the appointment as a perfect blend between the exec­utive and the legislature. According to him, the outgo­ing Speaker had demonstrated the capacity to be a fantastic manager of men. “I want to use this medium to express my heartfelt felicita­tion to the outgoing speaker of the House of Representatives, Rt Hon Femi Gbajabiamila, over his well deserved appointment as the Chief of Staff to President Bola Ahmed Tinubu (BAT). “Over the years, you have proven to be an astute politician with a clear vision as it is evident in the peaceful and progressive way you have been piloting the affairs of the Green Chamber. “I am confident that your new position will afford you a greater opportunity to support the Tinu­bu’s administration to deliver on its campaign promises anchored on “Renewed Hope.” May God Al­mighty guide you in your new task,” Mohammed said.